WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:12.576
Six numbers sit across the top of this dashboard, and most
people glance right past them. But one of them quietly
predicts whether you'll blow up your account. Let me show
you which.

2
00:00:13.176 --> 00:00:34.368
Start simple. Total P and L is the sum of every trade's
result in dollars. A win banks your target, a loss takes
the heat. And Samples is just how many trades are in the
picture. One quick warning. Below about a hundred trades,
every number up here is shaky, dominated by a few lucky or
unlucky outliers. You want a real sample before you trust
any of this.

3
00:00:34.968 --> 00:00:48.624
Win Rate is the share of your trades that reached the
target. But here's what beginners get backwards. A high
win rate is not the goal. Plenty of blown-up accounts had
eighty percent win rates. It only ever tells you how often
you win, never how much.

4
00:00:49.224 --> 00:00:55.680
Average Win Streak is how long your good runs tend to
last. Nice for confidence, but it's not where the danger
lives.

5
00:00:56.280 --> 00:01:22.104
This is the one that matters most. Loss Streak. The
longest run of losing trades you've had in a row. Why does
this single number predict ruin? Because a losing streak
is exactly what drains an account to zero. If you can only
stomach three losses in a row, but your history shows runs
of eight, you will bust before your edge ever gets the
chance to pay off. Everything in the survival lab, the
doomsday budget, your risk of ruin, is built around this
one number.

6
00:01:22.704 --> 00:01:30.192
And Span is simply the calendar stretch your data covers.
A quick reality check that your sample isn't all from one
freakishly good week.

7
00:01:30.792 --> 00:01:39.000
Glance at your P and L if you want. But respect the loss
streak. It's the number that decides whether you survive
long enough for your edge to actually win.
